## Color System

### Primary Brand Colors (from logo gradient)

| Token | Hex | HSL | Usage |
|-------|-----|-----|-------|
| `orderly-500` | `#3B5EEB` | `229 82% 58%` | Primary actions, links |
| `orderly-600` | `#2547D0` | `229 70% 48%` | Hover states |
| `orderly-700` | `#1E3A8A` | `224 64% 33%` | Active states |
| `orderly-900` | `#0F1629` | `225 45% 11%` | Dark backgrounds |
| `orderly-950` | `#0A0F1A` | `222 45% 7%` | Darkest background |

### Usage Rules

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT: Use semantic tokens
<div className="bg-background text-foreground">
<Button className="bg-primary">

// ❌ WRONG: Don't use raw hex values
<div style={{ background: '#3B5EEB' }}>
<div className="bg-[#0A0F1A]">
```

### Dark Mode First

Orderly uses **dark mode as the primary theme**. Always design for dark mode first, then ensure light mode works.

```tsx
// Default theme is dark in layout.tsx
<ThemeProvider defaultTheme="dark">
```

